---
import Container from "@components/container.astro";
import { Picture } from "astro:assets";
const { entry } = Astro.props;
const { Content } = await entry.render();
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";
import RelatedArticles from "@components/related-articles.astro";
import Link from "@components/ui/link.astro";
import Cta from "@components/cta.astro";
import JsonLd from "@components/JsonLd.astro";

const jsonLdData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  headline: ` What is the Best Open-Source Project Management Software ? ${Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]} vs ${Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]}`,
  datePublished: entry.data.publishDate.toISOString(),
  author: {
    "@type": "Person",
    name: entry.data.author,
  },
  keywords: entry.data.tags.join(", "),
  image: entry.data.image.src,
  description: entry.data.description,
};

---

<Container>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center mt-14">
    <h1
      class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold lg:tracking-tight mt-1 lg:leading-tight">
      What is the Best Open-Source Project Management Software ?
    </h1>
    <div class="mt-1">
      <span class="text-lg text-slate-500 italic">
        {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]} vs {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]} – But Is Worklenz the Better Choice ?
      </span>
    </div>
    <div
      class="flex gap-2 mt-3 items-center justify-center text-sm flex-wrap md:flex-nowrap">
      <span class="text-slate-400">
        {entry.data.author}
      </span>
      <span class="text-slate-400">•</span>
      <time
        class="text-slate-400"
        datetime={entry.data.publishDate.toISOString()}>
        {entry.data.publishDate.toDateString()}
      </time>
      <span class="text-slate-400 hidden md:block">•</span>
      <div class="w-full md:w-auto flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
        {
          entry.data.tags.map((tag) => (
            <span class="text-sm text-slate-500">#{tag}</span>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <Picture
      formats={["avif", "webp"]}
      src={entry.data.image.src}
      alt={entry.data.image.alt}
      width="1280"
      height="600"
      class="h-full w-full object-contain rounded-xl mt-6"
      transition:name={`post-img-${entry.slug}`}
    />
  </div>

  <div
    class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
    <div
      class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8">
      When it comes to managing projects efficiently, tools like {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]} and {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]} are often at the top of the list. Both offer powerful features that help teams stay organized, but they aren’t always the perfect fit for everyone. That’s where Worklenz comes in a flexible, open-source alternative that might just check all the boxes you didn’t even realize you needed.
Let’s compare the strengths and weaknesses of {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]} and {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]} while showing how Worklenz stands out as a practical and reliable third option for modern teams.
    </div>
    <!-- <div class="mx-auto prose mt-6 max-w-4xl prose-headings:mb-2 prose-headings:mt-8"> -->
    <h2>Comparing {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]} and {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]}</h2>
    <!-- </div> -->
    <div>
        {Object.entries(entry.data.tools).map(([toolName, toolData]: [string, any]) => (
          <div>
            <h3>{toolName}: {toolData.sub_title}</h3>
            <p>{toolData.main_content}</p>
            <b>Key Features of {toolName}</b>
            <ul>
              {toolData.features.map(feature => (
                <li>{feature}</li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))}
          </ul>
        </li>
      </div>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-800">Comparison Table: {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]} vs. {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]} vs. Worklenz</h1>
      <table class="table-auto w-full border-collapse border border-gray-300">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left font-medium text-gray-600">Feature</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left font-medium text-gray-600">{Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]}</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left font-medium text-gray-600">{Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]}</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left font-medium text-gray-600">Worklenz</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">Analytics</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].analytics_rate} <br> {entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].analytics_review}</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].analytics_rate} <br> {entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].analytics_review}</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐<br>Comprehensive and insightful</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">Customization</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].customization_rate} <br>{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].customization_review}</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].customization_rate} <br>{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].customization_review}</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">⭐⭐⭐⭐<br>Flexible yet straightforward </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">Collaboration Features</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].collaboration_features_rate} <br>{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].collaboration_features_review}</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].collaboration_features_rate} <br>{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].collaboration_features_review}</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ <br>Designed for seamless teamwork </td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">Self-Hosted Option</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{ entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].self_hosted ? '✔️' : '❌' }</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{ entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].self_hosted ? '✔️' : '❌' }</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">✔️</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">Open-Source</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{ entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].open_source ? '✔️' : '❌' }</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{ entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].open_source ? '✔️' : '❌' }</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">✔️ </td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">Pricing</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]].pricing}</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-gray-700">{entry.data.tools[Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]].pricing}</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-gray-700 text-center">Free & Paid plans <br><br> <Link class="mb-10" href="https://app.worklenz.com/auth/signup" size="sm"  block>Try for Free</Link></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>Meet the Third Option: Why Worklenz Could Be the Better Choice for Your Team</h2>
      <p>While {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]} and {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]} are widely recognized for their robust features, Worklenz offers something uniquely tailored for teams seeking a balance of simplicity, flexibility, and control. Here’s why it stands out</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <h3>Open-Source Advantage</h3>
          <p>
            Unlike {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]} and {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]}, Worklenz is fully open-source. This means users can customize it to meet their unique needs without being locked into proprietary restrictions. Whether you’re a developer wanting to tweak the software or a business aiming to align it with specific processes, the possibilities are endless.</p>
        </li>
        <li><h3>Self-Hosting for Complete Control</h3>
        <p>Worklenz allows businesses to host the platform on their servers, offering enhanced data security and compliance with industry regulations. This makes it an excellent choice for industries with strict privacy needs, such as healthcare, finance, or government organizations.</p>
        <h3>Why It Matters</h3>
        <p>For a company managing sensitive projects, relying on a third-party cloud solution might pose risks. Worklenz ensures that businesses retain full control of their data.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Designed for Simplicity and Scalability</h3>
          <p>Worklenz maintains a balance by providing an intuitive interface that’s easy to navigate. At the same time, it scales effortlessly to support growing teams or complex workflows.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>Final Thoughts - Key Takeaways</h2>
      <p>
        When comparing {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[0]}, {Object.keys(entry.data.tools || {})[1]}, and Worklenz, each tool has its strengths. However, Worklenz emerges as a top contender due to its flexibility, affordability, and open-source approach.
      </p>
      <p>Whether you’re managing campaigns, tracking content creation, or optimizing workflows, Worklenz provides the perfect balance of simplicity and power for marketing teams.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <Cta />
  <hr class="mx-auto max-w-4xl mt-16 mb-16" />

  <!-- Related Articles -->
  <RelatedArticles entry={entry}/>
  <!-- Schema Articles -->
  <JsonLd jsonLdData={jsonLdData} />
</Container>
